const description = 'Innovation with responsibility – Why European values matter in AI development and represent a competitive advantage.';

const fullContent = `
<p>"European AI can never compete with the US or China" – a narrative we hear often. We believe: It's fundamentally wrong.</p>

<p>Europe doesn't just have the chance, but the obligation to provide a third answer in the global AI discourse. One that doesn't pit innovation against responsibility but combines both.</p>

<h4>The Three Models</h4>

<p><strong>USA:</strong> "Move fast and break things"<br/>
Rapid growth, little regulation, venture-capital-driven. Innovation takes priority, consequences come later.</p>

<p><strong>China:</strong> Technological progress without regulatory barriers<br/>
Massive state investments, no privacy concerns, centralized control.</p>

<p><strong>Europe:</strong> "Innovation with Responsibility"<br/>
Excellence with ethics, technology with transparency, progress with fairness.</p>

<p>Three different approaches. Three different visions of the future.</p>

<h4>Why Europe Has a Unique Position</h4>

<p>Europe isn't the largest market. Not the most capital-rich ecosystem. Not the least regulated environment.</p>

<p>But Europe has something the others don't: <strong>Trust.</strong></p>

<p>Trust in institutions, in data protection, in fair markets, in democratic control. And in a world increasingly skeptical of tech giants, trust is the most valuable resource.</p>

<p><strong>European values aren't ballast – they're competitive advantages:</strong></p>

<ol>
  <li><strong>GDPR as quality mark</strong>: Data protection compliance signals: We take user protection seriously</li>
  <li><strong>EU AI Act as framework</strong>: Clear rules mean planning certainty</li>
  <li><strong>European hosting</strong>: Data stays in Europe, no third-country risks</li>
  <li><strong>Transparency and traceability</strong>: Systems whose decisions can be understood and audited</li>
</ol>

<h4>Innovation Without Compromise</h4>

<p>The biggest misconception: That regulated AI is inferior AI.</p>

<p><strong>The truth:</strong> The best AI systems aren't those with the most data, but those with the best domain understanding, the best evaluation, the best integration.</p>

<p>And this is where Europe plays to its strengths:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Excellent research</strong>: European universities and institutes world-leading</li>
  <li><strong>Domain expertise</strong>: Strong industry with deep technical knowledge</li>
  <li><strong>Quality culture</strong>: Focus on sustainable, robust solutions</li>
  <li><strong>Mittelstand</strong>: Real use cases instead of just consumer apps</li>
</ul>

<p>Europe can build AI that doesn't just impress but works – reliably, transparently, fairly.</p>

<h4>European Hosting: More Than a Buzzword</h4>

<p>Where data is stored isn't a technical detail question. It's a strategic decision with legal, business, and ethical implications.</p>

<p><strong>Why European hosting is critical:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Legal certainty</strong>: GDPR applies, Cloud Act doesn't</li>
  <li><strong>Data protection</strong>: No backdoors for third countries</li>
  <li><strong>Strategic autonomy</strong>: No dependence on US/China tech giants</li>
  <li><strong>Customer trust</strong>: Especially crucial in B2B</li>
</ul>

<p>At Klartext AI, we host exclusively in Europe – not because it's easier, but because it's right.</p>

<h4>The Future Belongs to the Trustworthy</h4>

<p>When we look back in ten years, one question will be decisive: Who do people trust with their data?</p>

<p>Systems that are fast? Or systems that are reliable?<br/>
Companies that are innovative? Or companies that are responsible?</p>

<p><strong>Our thesis</strong>: The future belongs to those who can do both – and that's exactly Europe's opportunity.</p>

<h4>European AI Sovereignty in Practice</h4>

<p>At Klartext AI, European AI sovereignty means:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Austrian and German hosting</strong>: Data stays in the EU</li>
  <li><strong>GDPR compliance by design</strong>: Not retrofitted, but built-in</li>
  <li><strong>EU AI Act ready</strong>: Prepared for coming regulation</li>
  <li><strong>Transparent systems</strong>: Traceable decisions</li>
  <li><strong>Local partnerships</strong>: European cloud providers, no Big Tech dependency</li>
</ul>

<p>This isn't a limitation. This is a quality promise.</p>

<h4>The Competitive Advantage of Regulation</h4>

<p>"But regulation slows innovation!" – A myth that won't die.</p>

<p><strong>Reality</strong>: Good regulation promotes innovation by:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Creating <strong>planning certainty</strong></li>
  <li>Guaranteeing <strong>fair competition</strong></li>
  <li>Building <strong>trust</strong></li>
  <li>Setting <strong>quality standards</strong></li>
</ul>

<p>Europe has the chance to become the global role model – not through the laxest rules, but through the smartest.</p>

<p><strong>At Klartext AI, we believe: European values aren't an obstacle to excellent AI – they're the prerequisite for it.</strong></p>
`;
